Method Detail

rendezvous

ProcessResult rendezvous(ProcessExecution execution1,
                         ProcessExecution execution2)
Called by the interpreter to acknowledge the process template that the rendezvou was successfull (the "who" also executed this process with current "actor" as "who").

Parameters:
execution1 - one of the two ProcessExecutions representing the running instance of this process.
execution2 - one of the two ProcessExecutions representing the running instance of this process.
Returns:
ProcessResult representing processes' states after the rendezvous acceptance. Whatever value is returned, it represents the state of both the processes.Explicitely, if this value is RUNNING, Interpreter should call the atomicLength method to get info about new processes' expected length and plan their finish. If this value equals to OK then both the processes have successfully finished.
